## Project Overview
The Library Management System is a console-based Java application developed using Object-Oriented Programming principles. It allows management of books and library members with features such as adding books, registering members, searching books, borrowing and returning books, and due date tracking.

The project is developed using Visual Studio Code and Java.

---

## Features
- Add new books to the library
- Register new library members
- Display all books and available books
- Search books by title or author
- Borrow and return books
- Due date calculation for borrowed books
- Menu-driven user interface

---

## Technologies Used
- Programming Language: Java
- IDE: Visual Studio Code (VS Code)
- Java Version: JDK 8 or above

